ActAeronautics Act
SubjectRegulations Amending the Designated Provisions Regulations and the Regulations Concerning Information Required by Foreign States
PrecisRegulations Amending the DESIGNATED PROVISIONS REGULATIONS and the REGULATIONS CONCERNING INFORMATION REQUIRED BY FOREIGN STATES in order to allow Canadian air carriers to comply with the "overflight" provisions of the Secure Flight program consistent with the Aeronautics Act, and Canadian privacy laws and to ensure that the privacy rights of travellers are balanced with new U.S. air transportation security measures.
